gomodel:SYNGO_4950  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: - K+-channel tetramerization domain-containing proteins (KCTDs) are auxiliary GABAB receptor (GBR) subunits.\n- Experiments were performed at the synaptic connection from medial habenula (MHb) to interpeduncular nucleus (IPN).\n- pre-embedding immunogold labeling, imaged with TEM. \"In MHb terminals in the rostral IPN, Cav2.3 and KCTD12b showed similar localization patterns, with peak particle densities in the active zone and a gradual decrease in density with increased distance from the active zone (Figure 3A,E).\"\n\n- Figure 2C: immunolabeling of WT and KCTD12b KO mice shows antibody specificity. Experimental description: Wild-type C57BL/6J mice(Jax, Bar Harbor, ME; #000664) purchased from Jackson Laboratory.\nPotassium channel tetramerisation domain-containing 12b\nAntibody: anti-KCTD12b (polyclonal, raised against a synthetic peptide comprised of the N-terminal amino acids 1-16 of KCTD12b) (1 ug/ul, 1 O/N, Bettler lab, Univ. Basel)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-01-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4950" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

